 essential cell biology isbn   essential cell biology bruce alberts dennis bray karen hopkin alexander d johnson alexander johnson julian lewis martin raff keith roberts peter walter  avg rating •   ratings by goodreads    hardcover isbn   isbn   publisher garland science  view all copies of this isbn edition     synopsis about this title essential cell biology provides an accessible introduction to the fundamental concepts of cell biology its lively writing and exceptional illustrations make it the ideal textbook for a first course in cell and molecular biology the text and figures are easytofollow accurate clear and engaging for the introductory student molecular detail has been kept to a minimum in order to provide the reader with a cohesive conceptual framework of the basic science that underlies our current understanding of biology the third edition is thoroughly updated scientifically yet maintains the academic level and size of the previous edition the book is accompanied by a media dvdrom with over  animations and videos all the figures from the book and a new selftest quizzing feature for students synopsis may belong to another edition of this title about the author bruce alberts received his phd from harvard university and is professor of biochemistry and biophysics at the university of california san francisco he is the editorinchief of science magazine for  years he served as president of the us national academy of sciences  dennis bray received his phd from massachusetts institute of technology and is currently an active emeritus professor at university of cambridge in  he was awarded the microsoft european science award karen hopkin received her phd in biochemistry from the albert einstein college of medicine and is a science writer in somerville massachusetts alexander johnson received his phd from harvard university and is professor of microbiology and immunology and director of the biochemistry cell biology genetics and developmental biology graduate program at the university of california san francisco julian lewis received his dphil from the university of oxford and is a principal scientist at the london research institute of cancer research uk martin raff received his md from mcgill university and is at the medical research council laboratory for molecular cell biology and cell biology unit and in the biology department at university college london keith roberts received his phd from the university of cambridge and is emeritus fellow at the john innes centre norwich peter walter received his phd from the rockefeller university in new york and is professor and chairman of the department of biochemistry and biophysics at the university of california san francisco and an investigator of the howard hughes medical institute review college and university professors who have used the previous editions of ecb will be pleased with the new edition  the format and organization are retained but have been infused with fresh images and updated material  it’s as if a trusted old friend has come back from an extended vacation with a bright new look and a refreshed attitude  the reader is at once comfortable with and excited by the changes new users of the textbook will find it accessible and approachable at the professorial and student levelsi highly recommend it to all cbelife sciences education readers who are also classroom educatorscbelife sciences education fall  this attractive accessible visually oriented text covers the fundamentals of cell biology required to understand biomedical and broader issues that affect students lives scitech book news august  praise of the second edition this book fills a critical niche in the pedagogical process of introducing cell biology and does an excellent job in reaching its objectivethe quarterly review of biology volume  an excellent example of designing a textbook for undergraduates and nonbiology majors it is clear well illustrated conversational in tone and enjoyable to read and browse throughestreams the second edition retains all the beauty of the first and it serves as an editorial model  a guide that shows us how serious authors prepare a new version of a serious book what makes for a great science education is not the amassing of facts but the understanding of concepts processes and syntheses and the realization that all our information about nature must be subject to testing and revision that is the kind of educational experience that students can acquire from the second edition of essential cell biology the textbook letter about this title may belong to another edition of this title buy new view book us  convert currency shipping us  within usa destination rates  speeds add to basket compare all  new copies  day return policy other popular editions of the same title featured edition isbn   x isbn    publisher garland science  softcover search for all books with this author and title customers who bought this item also bought top search results from the abebooks marketplace stock image  essential cell biology alberts brucebray dennislewis julianhopkin karenjohnson alexander published by florence kentucky usa taylor  francis  isbn   isbn   new hardcover quantity available   seller william horton phoenix az usa rating  book description florence kentucky usa taylor  francis  hardcover book condition new rd edition brand new book  fast delivery bookseller inventory  abe more information about this seller  ask bookseller a question buy new us  convert currency add to basket shipping us  within usa destination rates  speeds stock image  essential cell biology alberts bruce bray dennis hopkin karen johnson alexander d johnson alexander lewis julian raff martin roberts keith walter peter published by garland science isbn   isbn   new hardcover quantity available  seller balkanika online woodinville wa usa rating  book description garland science hardcover book condition new  cd included new book with very minor shelf wear student us editio